Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @coriander{1}(finely chopped) (stalks and all). Zest the @lime{1/2} and cut into wedges. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}(grated). Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

> We love good Lamb Meatballs with Beans and this deliciously simple, chef-curated recipe doesn't disappoint. Time to bust out the pots and pans!

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a large #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

In the meantime, pop the @lamb mince{200%g} into a #mixing bowl{}. Add half the coriander and season with a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Mix together well. Shape the lamb into three even sized meatballs per person.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

Heat a splash of @oil{splash} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. When hot, add the meatballs and cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn every minute or so. Drain off any excess fat.

When the meatballs are browned, transfer to a #plate{} (we will finish cooking them later!) and return the now empty frying pan to the heat. Add another drizzle of oil if dry, then stir in the onion and red pepper. Season with salt and pepper. Cook until the veggies are soft, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add the garlic, @Mexican style spice mix{1%packet} and @tomato puree{30%g} to the pan. Stirring, cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the mixed beans, @finely chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}, @water{300%ml} for the chilli, @beef stock powder{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} to the pan. Mix everything together. Return the meatballs to the pan and bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to a simmer, cover with a lid or #foil{}, and leave to gently bubble away until the meatballs are cooked and the sauce is thick, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle!

Once the meatballs are cooked, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest. Taste and season the chilli with salt and pepper. Share the rice between your #bowls{} then spoon the chilli on top. Sprinkle on the remaining coriander and the grated cheese. Serve the lime wedges to the side ready to be squeezed over. Enjoy!